<br>
The way the Brell community has leapt to defend not only me, but also really women and socially acceptable actions is incredibly uplifting.  Let us never forget that we are a community, people move in and out of it, but still, we set, reflect, and police what is acceptable.<br>
<br>
When I posted my rant, I was enraged.  Enraged at the treatment and the disrespect with which I was treated.  Truthfully, though, that would all have passed and an apology would have ended the whole matter.  I believe I am slow to anger and quick to forgiveness.  What I cannot forgive is the subsequent attacks by Akmorph on both my character and my guild.  The disdain which he treated me, women, and my guildmates with is beyond what I am willing to *let slide*.<br>
<br>
At some point we must all determine for ourselves what is worth fighting for both in real life and in game.<br>
<br>
At some point we all make mistakes and we learn from those mistakes.  <br>
<br>
I will not tolerate Akmorph, nor his treatment of others, but I hope that he takes from this a lesson, not only in Norrath, but one that will help him in real life too.  A lesson on community, respect, and human dignity.<br>
<br>
Hate with Honor <p>Creapiing V'Etch<BR>
